# Edu Forum Task: Link Questions to University Modules

This guide explains how to complete a custom two-part task for the Edu Forum:

> **Task 1 (Simple CRUD):** Allow students to optionally link their forum questions to a specific university module.
> **Task 2 (Business Logic):** Add format validation to ensure the module code strictly follows the university format (2 to 4 uppercase letters followed by exactly 3 digits, e.g., CS101, SE205).

---

## Task 1: Simple CRUD Operation

### Step 1: Add The Column To The Database
**File:** `sql/edu-hub/Questions-Table.sql`
Run this SQL command in your MySQL database to add the new column:
```sql
ALTER TABLE forum_questions
ADD COLUMN module_code VARCHAR(20) NULL;
```

### Step 2: Add The Input To The Ask Question Form
**File:** `app/views/User/edu-forum/add-question-view.php`
Find the form and replace your current "Course Module" HTML block with this clean, standardized input:
```html
<div class="form-group">
  <label for="module-code" class="form-label">Course Module (Optional)</label>
  <p class="form-description">
    If your question is related to a specific course module, specify it here.
  </p>
  <input id="module-code" class="form-input" type="text" name="module_code" placeholder="e.g., CS101">
</div>
```

### Step 3: Read The Field In The Controller
**File:** `app/controllers/Forum/ForumUserController.php`
Find the `createQuestion()` method. Update the `$data` array to capture the new input:
```php
$data = [
    'title'       => trim($_POST['title']),
    'category'    => trim($_POST['category']),
    'content'     => trim($_POST['description']),
    'module_code' => trim($_POST['module_code'] ?? ''), // <-- ADD THIS
    'tags'        => trim($_POST['tags'] ?? '')
];
```

### Step 4: Save The Field In The Model
**File:** `app/models/ForumModel.php`
Find the `createQuestion()` method. 

**1. Update the SQL INSERT query:**
```php
$sql = "INSERT INTO forum_questions (user_id, title, content, category, module_code, tags) 
        VALUES (:uid, :title, :content, :cat, :module_code, :tags)";
```

**2. Update the execute array to bind the value:**
```php
return $stmt->execute([
    ':uid'         => $userId,
    ':title'       => $data['title'],
    ':content'     => $data['content'],
    ':cat'         => $data['category'],
    ':module_code' => $data['module_code'], // <-- ADD THIS
    ':tags'        => $tags
]);
```

### Step 5: Display It On The Forum Feed
**File:** `app/views/User/edu-forum/all-questions-view.php`
Find the `foreach ($questions as $q):` loop. Display the module code inside the `<div class="question-tags">` container:
```php
